The food here is amazing! I’d come back any time, any day. Guacuco was actually my first meal of 2020 and it brought me back to leave. Although I am Hispanic, I was as still new to this type of cuisine and I loved every bit of it.  I ordered a passion fruit juice, a cheese empanada (which was huge), a shredded beef arepa with plantain in it (great savory and sweet combo), the cachapa ( a delicious sweet cheese and corn dish ) and the beef lasagna type dish. Lastly, we had the soup of the day which was an incredible chicken soup. We split the food between three of us and we were super full by the end.  On top of the great food, we also had very great service!

Complete disappointment, how anyone gives this place a good rating is beyond my understanding. If I could give this place less than a star rating I would.  I don't know if we just came on an off day or what, but ordered 3 arepas and it literally took them more than 30 minutes to get us our order.  What we ordered:  “Chevere - Perico, paisa cheese and black beans”  What I got was a plain egg with cheddar cheese and black beans, which I could have got from my bodga for $4, there was no onions or pepper or any flavor added to the eggs it was not paisa cheese it was completely bogus served on an undercooked arepa. Bland and boring.  “Mariscada - squid, shrimp, and mussels in red tomatoes sauce”  what I got a whole two small pieces of shrimp that and including all the seafood in this dish not fresh and was clearly previous frozen, some watered down tomato sauce and literally raw arepa dough on the side not even cut and didn’t bother to provide utensils. Didn’t bother to finish this because it was so bad.  “Pernil - pulled juicy pork shoulder with spices and cheddar cheese”  at least they got the cheese right on this one, but it wasn’t even melted and where was the “spices” this was completely bland and flavorless and served again on an undercooked doughy arepa.  I was pretty excited to have an arepa place close to home but this place is just terrible. The bartender was very sweet but doesn’t make up for the terrible food. I’ll just have to travel up to Caracas to get some descent Venezuelan food.

Let's talk about tequeños, and how Guacuco makes the best ones, hands down, I've ever tasted... This place was great! The perfect little spot to catch dinner with a friend or have a casual date night, with delicious (and STRONG) beverages, a menu of gems, and very affordable price tags to boot. If nothing else, stop in for a snack, and try the tequeños and the fun variety of sauces on the table and available in the menu to eat them with. That'll be satisfying enough to get you hooked on it's own.

We found out about Guacuco a month ago and since then we have visit the location at Irving Bk, where not only food is great but the staff is amazing! Today, before the snow storm, my boyfriend and I decided to get groom from Guacuco. This time however we were closer at the throop location, we went in and ordered our food, the guy that helped us was not as friendly as the people we are used to, however we didn’t put much thought to it, time went by and we realized that 40 minutes had passed, notice that at no point we were offered a “tour food would be ready soon” or a “sorry is taking longer” we weren’t even acknowledged; my boyfriend decided to ask the guy how much longer our order was going to take because we had been waiting more that 40 minutes, the guy said I don’t know, let me check; but the way he said it, it was definitely not the way you should approach your costumers. When finally our food was ready, the guy just placed it at our table and didn’t even say anything, not even a thank you for coming or sorry for the wait. We will not judge the whole company just for one person, however, WE WILL NOT RECOMMEND THIS LOCATION AT ALL.

This is gonna be a new comfort food favorite for me. Excellent selection of stuffed Venezuelan style Arepas, from vegetarian to all the tasty meats. The delicious, large home style Empanadas were a nice surprise. Finally a place that prepares better Empanadas than my mom. Bravo! Not easy to do.  The star of the show, as it usually is at any arepa place worth its salt, is the Cachapa entree. And this is the main reason I’ll keep coming back to this place. It’s that good.  They also have a nice selection of cocktails to wash it all down.  The only negative tip is the slow service. The staff were all very friendly and attentive, but it was a painfully long wait for a mojito from the bar. It could just have been a (unusually) bad night, but it would be my one concern with going there with a large group.

This is going to be my new go-to spot. The bartender was fabulous. He whipped up some delicious cocktails, all of which are reasonably priced! Their plantains are cooked to perfection. The dough for their empenadas is on point- slight sweetness to it. Their arepa's are out of this world. They have one with beans, plantains, shredded beef... Tasty! Also, they prepare food to order so it comes out in perfect timing. Order a bunch of arepa's and empenadas and you'll be happy. It's also very big inside. The bar is full size and lots of space for big parties or just groups of two. Happy it's in Bed-Stuy!
